service.name: Youth Disability Supplement
service.description: Youth Disability Supplement (YDS) is available to recipients of Disability Support Pension who are 21 years of age or under or Youth Allowance and ABSTUDY recipients who are 21 years of age and under and have been assessed by an Employment Services Assessment (ESAt) or Job Capacity Assessment (JCA) as having a partial capacity to work of less than 30 hours per week.
